3.2.1.3 Tai Chi
The meta-analysis conducted by
Rampengan et al. (2024)
in 2024 included 5 RCTs with 584 individuals diagnosed with MCI, in which Tai Chi was part of the pooled analysis. The review found that Tai Chi intervention significantly improved MMSE scores, thereby enhancing cognitive function (SMD 0.36, 95% CI 0.18 to 0.54) compared to the conventional exercise group, patients who received fall prevention and cognitive education, and the group that received no treatment, in individuals with MCI.

